annotation.TEXT: Push!
Hello, this is SomeGuy712x, and welcome to...
To be continued... Yo!
Good thing my cape was open when I got hit there. Also, I'll pointlessly grab these 1-ups I don't need. (Oh, I just noticed that I'm at 99 coins as well as at 99 lives. That's neat.)
Now, I'm not going in that pipe up there this time, and will instead stay down here, so we can see the rest of this main area.

Surprisingly, I ended up playing through most of Solar Jetman before I found a chest containing bananas to use for that clip there. I ended up finding those near the beginning of hidden planet 13, Urownd, which you can warp to from planet 8, Shishkebab.
Oh, nice! I was hoping to get at least 40 there for the bonus game!
Yeah, lots of Boo Beams, and a mysterious floating yellow parakoopa, and what I assume is death water. Yeah, it's gotta be delicious lime-green death water.
Nope, I hit the 63-coin limit before I could make it. Oh, well.
DOUBLE KILL!
Alright, so the secret exit is done, and I'm assuming it'll just reveal the path to the Top Banana Zone, right?
Yep, one of my fireballs went right through the lower-right corner there!
Ow! I just had to try to thwack that plant, didn't I? Well, at least I did kill the plant. Oh, does this message say anything different?
How did you get that parakoopa to jog in place in midair like that, anyway? That's really weird! Another funny hex edit, perhaps?
Hi, Yoshi! Don't worry. I'm not gonna toss you into a pit this time.

But, I am gonna just leave Yoshi behind right there. Now, while up here, keep going to the right, and jump over a 6-tile high wall along the way (having a cape to fly over it helps), then jump again when you bump into something off screen.
Yeah, there was a moon up there! However, if you keep going to the right after that, you'll fall off the level, so don't do that. (Good thing I was able to Start+Select out!)
Right away, I see that the auto-scrolling effect has been removed. Now I wonder if anything special has been done with layer 2 here...
Well, I believe that's a fail. I probably would've had better luck if I had gotten the screen to scroll up first.
Whoa, that river formed quickly! Oh, but what happened to DP3's level dot?
Goal tape average so far: 300 / 8 = 37.5 stars each.
So, yeah. The demo's inputs weren't tweaked, but the enemies were, which fits with Super Tweak World's theme perfectly. Alright, now let's return to where I left off last time...
Come on, Mario. Don't fumble with the vine now.

But, before I get to the voting results, there's something in NO Block Randomness that the 87th guy who practices medicine on a particular food that goes well with syrup and/or butter (besides pancakes) informed me about...
Move faster, Golden Swooper Football Pokey!
So, where should I head next? Donut Plains 3, Green Switch Palace, or Donut Secret 1? Place your votes now!
No Yoshis because... reasons.
Looks the same as usual to me. Alright, let's get the secret exit now.
I think I might've just cloned straight up there. Also, I've gotta keep thwacking this Buzzy to reset its stun timer.
Yeah, that worked. But, I don't think there's anything of interest up here. (If there is, let me know.)
I'll let that koopa in the middle live this time.
And there's yet another 40. I've been getting a lot of 40s lately, which isn't a bad thing, I guess.
Well, I'm not getting across Springfield Gorge that way. But, can I make it without a cape by doing a bat bounce?
I do believe I just cloned up and to the right there.

There didn't seem to be any obvious way to get over that large pit. I was able to bounce off of that bat in this case, and flying would certainly be an option, but what if I'd already slain all of the Swoopers and didn't have a cape?
Umm... What's this?
Alright, now which of the four newly available levels will I be playing next? Let's find out...
Well, the turn blocks up there are kind of shaped like a banana. But, what's with the off-center screen position? Also, is it possible to even get on top of that banana?
No, these rooms all look the same so far... I guess I'll produce some spiral power with these coins, or something...
Can I go all the way back through the spiral and reach the brown block again?
BGM: Pipe Dream (NES) - Game Music 01
WHEEEE!!!

By the way, I included all of the silly votes from the previous three episodes here, but I only included the serious votes from last episode, since the number of levels on the ballot had changed there.

Well, without a cape, maybe a sprinting jump could make it, but I'll have to test that later. Anyway, did you notice the Buzzy to the right of the exit pipe? Here, I'll do some screen scrolling so you guys can get a better look.
Bye, Yoshi! Hey, waffledoctor87, I think you should set this level to "Vertical scroll at will". Can I at least fly to make the screen scroll up here?
Pfft... So much for trying to follow a kicked shell here. The Swoopers are in the worst spots for that. At least I can get my feather back right here.
So, you've added lava with Podoboos here. Too bad Yoshi's graphics don't agree with the vertical Podoboos' graphics...
...Yeah, it's this again. However, this time, the title demo has been tweaked! I forgot to show this in the previous episode, so I'm showing it now!
MOOOOOONNNNN!!!
Moon count: 1
Whoa, what's with the green ghost-fire plant in midair there? Well, anyway, if this is anything like the original Donut Ghost House...
Nope. Same message. Also, I noticed a Boo Beam here too, so I'd better pay attention for those.
...Oh, yeah. One more thing...
I'll go with Donut Plains 2, which was winning the poll after episodes 3 and 4, before Top Banana Zone and Donut House 1 got revealed in episode 5.

Yeah, there's a Buzzy in the wall just to the right of the exit pipe that just simply falls off the screen. That Buzzy is indeed there in the vanilla SMW, but it'll always fall out of bounds before the slow auto-scroll gets close enough for you to see it. Who knows why Nintendo put that Buzzy there...
Nuts. I got shoved into the side exit there. But, maybe I can fly around the right side of the banana?
Alright, let's just finish this level.
It's not too far into the level, so I didn't see any need to speed up the footage here.
Speaking of bananas...
Yep! Okay, now for that normal exit...
That opens up Green Switch Palace, as expected. Now let's go back for the normal exit, as usual.
Also, there was a late vote for Conway's Game of Super Koopas.
Alright, I've got this treasure chest, and I've gotta bring it to the ship to see what's inside of it... (Come on, please be a pile of gems or Easter Island statues...)
A lousy 8 coins from that multi-coin block.
Well, at least this pipe still works. Has this room been tweaked at all?
Nice! Now, watch the lower-right corner when I slow down the footage here.
Well, I'm not going to play DP3 right now, but it will be on the voting ballot for next time. Now, I'm only about 6 minutes into the video, so I think I can do one more level today...
Umm... I'm kinda having a hard time seeing what's above me here-- WAH!!!

Are any of the rooms besides the first room of this place tweaked at all?

And, as expected, that opens the path leading to Donut House 1, which means I won't need to go around the long way to get to the other side of Donut Plains anymore.
Yeah, that works, and you don't even need to be sprinting. However, without a cape or bat, you're outta luck. waffledoctor87, you should probably add some things there.

I'm just gonna let that Golden Swooper Football Pokey walk off the edge here...

Wow, I'm surprised that one ghost I passed through didn't hit me there, which would've screwed me out of being able to go this way! So, yeah. It looks like the path to the secret exit is the same here.
Whoa! Yeah, flying lets me scroll the screen up, just in time to nearly be blasted by a cannon that I previously wasn't aware of.
Yeah, they're all brown used blocks, so I failed to make a factory there. That's a bummer.
Oh, this is different, and somewhat interesting. I've gotta bounce off these duders to get across.
14 coins from that multi-coin block.
